<h1>Problem 681 - 1999 Russia</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>In a certain finite nonempty school, every boy likes at least one girl. Prove that we can find a set \(S\) of strictly more than half the students in the school such that each boy in S likes an odd number of girls in \(S\).</p>
